"{\"uid\": \"fansided.com-posts-2024-paris-olympics-surfing-round-1\", \"entities\": [{\"sentence\": \"Fans around the world are eagerly awaiting the opening rounds of the2024 Paris Olympic Gamessurfing competition.\", \"from\": 0, \"to\": 112, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"However, unlike the other events in the Summer Olympic Games, the date is not written in stone.\", \"from\": 113, \"to\": 208, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Sohow does the surfing competition work?\", \"from\": 209, \"to\": 249, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Nearly 10,000 miles away from the home site of the Paris Games, the surfing athletes are preparing to ride a monster wave in Tahiti.\", \"from\": 250, \"to\": 382, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 375, \"end\": 381, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tahiti\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.9393123425910603e-14, \"text\": \"Tahiti\", \"types\": [\"Q23442\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tahiti\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tahiti\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The exact launch of their competition will depend on weather and ocean conditions.\", \"from\": 383, \"to\": 465, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The very first day for \\u00e2\\u0080\\u009cThe Call\\u00e2\\u0080\\u009d will be July 27.\", \"from\": 466, \"to\": 520, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"If that day\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s forecast looks promising the competition will be given the go-ahead.\", \"from\": 521, \"to\": 605, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Round one will see all surfers on both the men's and women\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s sides take the water.\", \"from\": 607, \"to\": 691, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"They will be in heats of three with the winner moving straight to the third round.\", \"from\": 692, \"to\": 774, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The two other athletes from each heat will have to battle it out once again in the second round based on scores, with the loser of that heat going home.\", \"from\": 775, \"to\": 927, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Men:Heat 1- Ethan Ewing (AUS), Tim Elter (GER), and Jordy Smith (RSA)Heat 2- Joan Duru (FRA), Jack Robinson (AUS), and Matthew McGillivray (RSA)Heat 3- Alonso Correa (PER), Filipe Toledo (BRA), and Kanoa Igarashi (JPN)Heat 4- Gabriel Medina (BRA), Connor O'Leary (JPN), and Bryan Perez (ESA)Heat 5- Ramzi Boukhiam (MAR), Billy Stairmand (NZL), and Jo\\u00c3\\u00a3o Chianca (BRA)Heat 6- Andy Criere (ESP), John John Florence (USA), and Alan Cleland (MEX)Heat 7- Kauli Vaast (FRA), Lucca Mesinas (PER), and Griffin Colapinto (USA)Heat 8- Rio Waida (INA), Leonardo Fioravanti (ITA), and Inaba Reo (JPN)  Women:Heat 1\\tYolanda Hopkins (POR), Caroline Marks (USA), and Sarah Baum (RSA)Heat 2\\tSol Aguirre (PER), Janire Etxabarri (ESP), and Vahine Fierro (FRA)Heat 3\\tAnat Lelior (ISR), Sanoa Dempfle-Olin (AUS), and Tyler Wright (AUS)Heat 4\\tTatiana Weston-Webb (BRA), Molly Picklum (AUS), and Caitlin Simmers (USA)Heat 5\\tJohanne Defay (FRA), Brisa Hennessy (CRC), and Candelaria Resano (NCA)Heat 6\\tTain\\u00c3\\u00a1 Hinckel (BRA), Camilla Kemp (GER), and Luana Silva (BRA)Heat 7\\tNadia Erostarbe (ESP), Siqi Yang (CHN), and Saffi Vette (NZL)Heat 8\\tCarissa Moore (USA), Teresa Bonvalot (POR), and Matsuda Shino (JPN)  There are some past Olympic and World champions in the mix this year in Tahiti.\", \"from\": 929, \"to\": 2194, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 954, \"end\": 957, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australia\", \"score\": 0.9999999191168204, \"rank\": 7.560696845618487e-08, \"text\": \"AUS\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australia\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australia\"}, {\"begin\": 964, \"end\": 969, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Leo_Elter\", \"score\": 0.8350804352520854, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Elter\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q14128148\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Leo_Elter\", \"dbpedia\": \"